swSysSystemId.name: swSysSystemId
swSysSystemId.description: The unique identifier assigned to this system during manufacturing.

swSysSystemName.name: swSysSystemName
swSysSystemName.description: The text string describing this system.

swSysSystemManufacturer.name: swSysSystemManufacturer
swSysSystemManufacturer.description: The text string describing the manufacturer of this system.

swSysSystemHardwareRevision.name: swSysSystemHardwareRevision
swSysSystemHardwareRevision.description: The revision level of the system, contained in two octets. The first octet indicates the artwork revision, and the second octet indicates the rework level.

swSysSystemMemorySize.name: swSysSystemMemorySize
swSysSystemMemorySize.description: The amount of memory (RAM), in bytes, present on the system processor board.

swSysSystemFlashMemorySize.name: swSysSystemFlashMemorySize
swSysSystemFlashMemorySize.description: The amount of flash memory, in bytes, present on the system processor board.

swSysSystemNvMemorySize.name: swSysSystemNvMemorySize
swSysSystemNvMemorySize.description: The amount of non-volatile memory, in bytes, present on the system processor board.

swSysSystemSoftwareRevision.name: swSysSystemSoftwareRevision
swSysSystemSoftwareRevision.description: The revision number of the Switching Systems software. Each byte indicates the following: byte 0: major release number. byte 1: minor release number. byte 2: update number. byte 3: bits 7-6: release type. bits 5-0: supplemental identifier.

swSysSystemBuildTime.name: swSysSystemBuildTime
swSysSystemBuildTime.description: The build time of the system software.

swSysSystemSnmpRevision.name: swSysSystemSnmpRevision
swSysSystemSnmpRevision.description: The revision number of the SNMP agent implementation.

swSysSystemRequestedSnmpMode.name: swSysSystemRequestedSnmpMode
swSysSystemRequestedSnmpMode.description: This object describes the requested SNMP mode for the system. The value of this object indicates the mode that will become effective following a reboot of the system. Note that only a subset of the above values may be valid for some systems.

swSysSystemCurrentSnmpMode.name: swSysSystemCurrentSnmpMode
swSysSystemCurrentSnmpMode.description: This object describes the currently active SNMP mode for the system. Note that only a subset of the above values may be valid for some systems.

swSysSystemAction.name: swSysSystemAction
swSysSystemAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other(1). Setting this object to the value reset(2) causes a reset of the system. Setting this object to the value nvReset(3) causes the system's non-volatile configuration to be reset to the default values. The value other(1) is not a vaild value for set operations.

swSysSystemOvertemperature.name: swSysSystemOvertemperature
swSysSystemOvertemperature.description: This object indicates the current overtemperature status for the system. If the system does not support overtemperature detection, this object returns notSupported.

swSysSystemFanFailure.name: swSysSystemFanFailure
swSysSystemFanFailure.description: This object indicates the current fan status for the system. If the system does not support fan failure detection, this object returns notSupported.

swSysSystemProtocolMask.name: swSysSystemProtocolMask
swSysSystemProtocolMask.description: This object is a bit mask that indicates which protocols exist in the software image currently loaded in memory. The value of this OBJECT is a sum. It initially takes on the value 0, then for each protocol bit as defined below, 2 raised to the value of the (bit position - 1) is added to the sum. The following bits are defined: IP_ROUTING 0x00000001 IPX_ROUTING 0x00000002 DDP_ROUTING 0x00000004 A value of 0x00000000 indicates the standard switching software.

swSysSystemConsoleAccess.name: swSysSystemConsoleAccess
swSysSystemConsoleAccess.description: This object determines whether another device can remotely access the system console via Telnet, Rlogin, or modem port. An existing remote session will not be terminated when this value is modified.

swSysSystemConsoleReadPwd.name: swSysSystemConsoleReadPwd
swSysSystemConsoleReadPwd.description: This object is the console read-access password.

swSysSystemConsoleWritePwd.name: swSysSystemConsoleWritePwd
swSysSystemConsoleWritePwd.description: This object is the console write-access password. The read-write community string is required for access to this object.

swSysSystemConsoleAdminPwd.name: swSysSystemConsoleAdminPwd
swSysSystemConsoleAdminPwd.description: This object is the console admin-access password. The read-write community string is required for access to this object.

swSysSystemDateTime.name: swSysSystemDateTime
swSysSystemDateTime.description: The current date and time as reflected by the system clock in the format mm/dd/yy hh:mm:ss xM.

swSysSystemDSTime.name: swSysSystemDSTime
swSysSystemDSTime.description: This parameter specifies the displacement, in minutes, from non-daylight savings time. The swSysDSTime object, along with the swSysTimeZone object, allows the system to support Universal time for network communications spanning different time zones.

swSysSystemTimeZone.name: swSysSystemTimeZone
swSysSystemTimeZone.description: This parameter specifies, in minutes, displacement of the system west of Greenwich. A negative number for this parameter indicates how many minutes displacement east of Greenwich the site is located. A positive number indicates the number of minutes west of Greenwich.

swSysSystemCurrentFddiStationMode.name: swSysSystemCurrentFddiStationMode
swSysSystemCurrentFddiStationMode.description: This object describes the current FDDI station mode for systems that support multi-station mode.

swSysSystemRequestedFddiStationMode.name: swSysSystemRequestedFddiStationMode
swSysSystemRequestedFddiStationMode.description: This object describes the requested FDDI station mode for systems that support multi-station mode. The requested mode will become current during the next system reboot.

swSysSystemLogEntryCurrentCount.name: swSysSystemLogEntryCurrentCount
swSysSystemLogEntryCurrentCount.description: The number of entries currently recorded in the system log.

swSysSystemLogMaxSize.name: swSysSystemLogMaxSize
swSysSystemLogMaxSize.description: The maximum number of events that can be recorded in the system log.

swSysSystemLogSeverityThreshold.name: swSysSystemLogSeverityThreshold
swSysSystemLogSeverityThreshold.description: This object determines the miminum serverety level of events recorded in the system log. For example, if the swSysSysteLogSeverityThreshold is set to errors(3) than only events which have serverity levels of error(3) or higher will be recorded.

swSysSystemLogTable.name: swSysSystemLogTable
swSysSystemLogTable.description: This table provides information on recorded system events.

swSysSystemLogIndex.name: swSysSystemLogIndex
swSysSystemLogIndex.description: The index of the log entry relative to this entry.

swSysSystemLogSeverityLevel.name: swSysSystemLogSeverityLevel
swSysSystemLogSeverityLevel.description: Indicates the severity level of the log entry.

swSysSystemLogDateTime.name: swSysSystemLogDateTime
swSysSystemLogDateTime.description: Indicates the date and time of the log event and is formatted as follows: MM:DD:YY HH:MM:SS.

swSysSystemLogFacility.name: swSysSystemLogFacility
swSysSystemLogFacility.description: The facility which entered the event in the log. fcmlmm(6) represents those events which may be common to the Lanplex Management Module (LMM) and the FDDI Concentrator Module (FCM). lmmfddi(6) represents those events specific to the FDDI portion of the LMM and lmmboard represents general events logged by the LMM.

swSysSystemBaseMACAddress.name: swSysSystemBaseMACAddress
swSysSystemBaseMACAddress.description: The base MAC address for the system.

swSysSystemMACAddressCount.name: swSysSystemMACAddressCount
swSysSystemMACAddressCount.description: The number of MAC addresses allocated to this system.

swSysSystemChassisSerialNumber.name: swSysSystemChassisSerialNumber
swSysSystemChassisSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the chassis.

swSysSystemFPMemorySize.name: swSysSystemFPMemorySize
swSysSystemFPMemorySize.description: The amount of frame processor memory (RAM), in bytes.

swSysSystemBufferSize.name: swSysSystemBufferSize
swSysSystemBufferSize.description: The amount of buffer memory, in bytes.

swSysSlotCount.name: swSysSlotCount
swSysSlotCount.description: The count of slots in the chassis.

swSysSlotTable.name: swSysSlotTable
swSysSlotTable.description: A list of slot entries. A single entry exists in this list for each slot in the chassis.

swSysSlotEntry.name: swSysSlotEntry
swSysSlotEntry.description: A slot entry contains information about a particular slot.

swSysSlotIndex.name: swSysSlotIndex
swSysSlotIndex.description: The index of the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotBoardType.name: swSysSlotBoardType
swSysSlotBoardType.description: The type of board residing in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotBoardRevision.name: swSysSlotBoardRevision
swSysSlotBoardRevision.description: The revision number of the board in the slot identified by this entry. If the slot is empty, or the revision is unknown this object returns a zero length string.

swSysSlotBoardStatus.name: swSysSlotBoardStatus
swSysSlotBoardStatus.description: The status of the board in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotBoardName.name: swSysSlotBoardName
swSysSlotBoardName.description: The text string describing the board in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotBoardNameAbbrev.name: swSysSlotBoardNameAbbrev
swSysSlotBoardNameAbbrev.description: The abbreviation used to describe the board in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotEthernetPortCount.name: swSysSlotEthernetPortCount
swSysSlotEthernetPortCount.description: The count of ethernet ports in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotFddiMacCount.name: swSysSlotFddiMacCount
swSysSlotFddiMacCount.description: The count of FDDI MACs in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotFddiPortCount.name: swSysSlotFddiPortCount
swSysSlotFddiPortCount.description: The count of FDDI ports in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotOvertemperature.name: swSysSlotOvertemperature
swSysSlotOvertemperature.description: This object indicates the current overtemperature status for the slot. If the slot does not support overtemperature detection, this object returns notSupported.

swSysSlotTokenRingPortCount.name: swSysSlotTokenRingPortCount
swSysSlotTokenRingPortCount.description: The count of TokenRing ports in the slot identified by this entry.

swSysSlotBoardRevStr.name: swSysSlotBoardRevStr
swSysSlotBoardRevStr.description: This revision number of the board in the slot identified by this entry. If the slot is empty, or the revision is unknown this object returns a zero length string. The format of the string is XX.YY, where the XX is the major revision (artwork), the YY is the minor revision (rework)

swSysSlotConverterBad.name: swSysSlotConverterBad
swSysSlotConverterBad.description: This object indicates the current status +12V->+5V converter for the slot. If the slot does not support +12V->+5V converter detection, this object returns notSupported.

swSysControlPanelHardwareRevision.name: swSysControlPanelHardwareRevision
swSysControlPanelHardwareRevision.description: An 8-bit value specifying the revision level of the control panel hardware.

swSysControlPanelSoftwareRevision.name: swSysControlPanelSoftwareRevision
swSysControlPanelSoftwareRevision.description: An 8-bit value specifying the revision level of the control panel software.

swSysControlPanelLines.name: swSysControlPanelLines
swSysControlPanelLines.description: The number of lines in the control panel display.

swSysControlPanelColumns.name: swSysControlPanelColumns
swSysControlPanelColumns.description: The number of columns in the control panel display.

swSysControlPanelText.name: swSysControlPanelText
swSysControlPanelText.description: The currently displayed text in the control panel display.

swSysControlPanelAccess.name: swSysControlPanelAccess
swSysControlPanelAccess.description: This object determines whether modifications to system configuration are allowed via the Control Panel

swSysPowerSupplyCount.name: swSysPowerSupplyCount
swSysPowerSupplyCount.description: The count of power supplies in the system.

swSysPowerSupplyStatusTable.name: swSysPowerSupplyStatusTable
swSysPowerSupplyStatusTable.description: A list of power supply status entries.

swSysPowerSupplyStatusEntry.name: swSysPowerSupplyStatusEntry
swSysPowerSupplyStatusEntry.description: A power supply status entry contains information about a particular power supply.

swSysPowerSupplyStatusIndex.name: swSysPowerSupplyStatusIndex
swSysPowerSupplyStatusIndex.description: The unique index of the power supply identified by this entry.

swSysPowerSupplyStatus.name: swSysPowerSupplyStatus
swSysPowerSupplyStatus.description: This object represents the power supply status. The value is a sum. It initially takes on the value 0, then for each type which is active, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table. For the 6000 Backbone Aggregator an over temp for power supply 1 and power supply 2 will be reported as a power supply 1 Over Temperature Failure, and a fan failure will be reported as a power supply 2 Over Temperature Failure. Failure Type Power AC Failure 0 Plus 5 Failure 1 Plus 12 Failure 2 Over Temperature Failure 3 Power Supply Inserted 4 Power Supply Extracted 5

swSysPowerSupplyStatusSupported.name: swSysPowerSupplyStatusSupported
swSysPowerSupplyStatusSupported.description: This object represents the various power supply status types which are supported. The value is a sum. It initially takes on the value 0, then for each type which is supported, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Failure Type Power AC Failure 0 Plus 5 Failure 1 Plus 12 Failure 2 Over Temperature Failure 3 Power Supply Inserted 4 Power Supply Extracted 5 This object used in conjunction with the swSysPowerSupplyStatus object for a given power supply provide a complete picture of the status of the power supply.

swSysSnmpAgentId.name: swSysSnmpAgentId
swSysSnmpAgentId.description: The unique id for this SNMP agent within the system.

swSysSnmpInternalAgentTrapMask.name: swSysSnmpInternalAgentTrapMask
swSysSnmpInternalAgentTrapMask.description: This value is a bit string that indicates which traps are enabled for transmit to other agents in the system. The octet string value is treated as a 64-bit integer value. The value is a sum. It initially takes on the value 0, then for each trap which is enabled, 2 raised to the value of (swSysAgentTrapDescriptionIndex - 1) for that trap is added to the sum.

swSysSnmpInternalAgentTrapDestinationMas.name: swSysSnmpInternalAgentTrapDestinationMask
swSysSnmpInternalAgentTrapDestinationMas.description: A value which indicates to which other agents in the system traps should be sent. The value is a sum. It initially takes on the value 0, then for each agent which is to receive traps, 2 raised to the value of (swSysSnmpAgentId - 1) for that agent is added to the sum. Note that only traps which are enabled according to the value of the swSysSnmpInternalAgentTrapMask object will be forwarded, and that each trap which is forwarded will be transmitted to each agent identified by this mask.

swSysSnmpProxyInternalRequests.name: swSysSnmpProxyInternalRequests
swSysSnmpProxyInternalRequests.description: This object determines if this agent will proxy requests to other agents in the system. If the value of this object is true(1), this agent will proxy requests to other agents in the chassis.

swSysSnmpInternalProxyRequestMaxAge.name: swSysSnmpInternalProxyRequestMaxAge
swSysSnmpInternalProxyRequestMaxAge.description: The maximum time, in seconds, an internal proxy request will remain queued waiting for a response before being discarded. Note that when the value of swSysSnmpProxyInternalRequests is false(2), the value of this object is ignored.

swSysSnmpProxyInternalTraps.name: swSysSnmpProxyInternalTraps
swSysSnmpProxyInternalTraps.description: This object determines if this agent will generate proxy traps for those traps received from other agents in the system. If the value of this object is true(1), this agent will generate proxy traps for those received from other agents in the chassis. Note that agents will not proxy traps to other agents within the system to prevent looping of traps.

swSysSnmpInternalProxyTable.name: swSysSnmpInternalProxyTable
swSysSnmpInternalProxyTable.description: A list of SNMP internal agent proxy entries. An entry in this table exists for each agent in the system that can be reached by this agent via the internal proxy mechanism.

swSysSnmpInternalProxyEntry.name: swSysSnmpInternalProxyEntry
swSysSnmpInternalProxyEntry.description: An entry identifies the communities available for communicating with another agent in the system via the internal proxy mechanism.

swSysSnmpInternalProxyAgentId.name: swSysSnmpInternalProxyAgentId
swSysSnmpInternalProxyAgentId.description: The id of the agent identified by this entry.

swSysSnmpInternalProxyAccessClass.name: swSysSnmpInternalProxyAccessClass
swSysSnmpInternalProxyAccessClass.description: The access to MIB objects supported by the agent identified by this entry provided by this agent, when using the community string identified by the corresponding value of swSysSnmpInternalProxyCommunity.

swSysSnmpInternalProxyCommunity.name: swSysSnmpInternalProxyCommunity
swSysSnmpInternalProxyCommunity.description: A community which allows access to MIB objects supported by the agent identified by this entry.

swSysAgentRequestMaxAge.name: swSysAgentRequestMaxAge
swSysAgentRequestMaxAge.description: The maximum time, in seconds, a local SNMP request will remain queued waiting for a response before being discarded.

swSysAgentProxyRemoteSmtRequests.name: swSysAgentProxyRemoteSmtRequests
swSysAgentProxyRemoteSmtRequests.description: This object determines if this agent will proxy SMT requests to other FDDI stations. If the value of this object is true(1), this agent will proxy SMT requests to other stations. Note that only a subset of the above values may be valid for some systems.

swSysAgentRemoteSmtProxyRequestMaxAge.name: swSysAgentRemoteSmtProxyRequestMaxAge
swSysAgentRemoteSmtProxyRequestMaxAge.description: The maximum time, in seconds, an SMT proxy request will remain queued waiting for a response before being discarded. Note that when the value of swSysAgentProxyRemoteSmtRequests is false(2), the value of this object is ignored.

swSysAgentProxyRemoteSmtEvents.name: swSysAgentProxyRemoteSmtEvents
swSysAgentProxyRemoteSmtEvents.description: This object determines if this agent will generate traps for SMT events occuring at other stations. If the value of this object is true(1), this agent will generate traps for all SMT events, those which occur locally, and those which occur at other stations. If the value of this object is false(2), this agent will only generate traps for events which occur locally. Note that only a subset of the above values may be valid for some systems.

swSysAgentTrapDescriptionTable.name: swSysAgentTrapDescriptionTable
swSysAgentTrapDescriptionTable.description: This table contains a listing of trap descriptions for each trap supported by this agent. This provides a relationship between a trap index, and the trap enterprise oid and trap number for a given trap. In all cases except for the MIB-2 generic traps, the enterprise under which a trap is defined is the same as that appearing in the ENTERPRISE portion of the trap.

swSysAgentTrapDescriptionTableEntry.name: swSysAgentTrapDescriptionTableEntry
swSysAgentTrapDescriptionTableEntry.description: Information relating a trap index to a specific trap enterprise oid and trap number.

swSysAgentTrapDescriptionIndex.name: swSysAgentTrapDescriptionIndex
swSysAgentTrapDescriptionIndex.description: A unique index corresponding to the trap described by this entry. This value of this object corresponding to a particular trap will remain constant accross system resets.

swSysAgentTrapEnterprise.name: swSysAgentTrapEnterprise
swSysAgentTrapEnterprise.description: The enterpise under which the trap identified by this entry is defined.

swSysAgentTrapNumber.name: swSysAgentTrapNumber
swSysAgentTrapNumber.description: The number of the trap identified by this entry, within the enterprise where it is defined.

swSysAgentTrapDestinationTable.name: swSysAgentTrapDestinationTable
swSysAgentTrapDestinationTable.description: This table contains information specifying which traps will be transmitted to a given destination address. The table is indexed by the destination address type and destination address. Each entry in the table with a status of valid identifies a set of traps which, when generated, will be transmitted to the corresponding destination address listed in that entry.

swSysAgentTrapDestinationTableEntry.name: swSysAgentTrapDestinationTableEntry
swSysAgentTrapDestinationTableEntry.description: Information relating a set of traps and a destination address to which each trap in ths set will be transmitted when it is generated. To create a new entry, set a non-existent instance of swSysAgentTrapDestinationTrapMask to a valid value. To remove an entry, set the instance of swSysAgentTrapDestinationEntryStatus for the entry to invalid(2).

swSysAgentTrapDestinationAddressType.name: swSysAgentTrapDestinationAddressType
swSysAgentTrapDestinationAddressType.description: The type of address identified by this entry.

swSysAgentTrapDestinationAddress.name: swSysAgentTrapDestinationAddress
swSysAgentTrapDestinationAddress.description: The address, of the type specified by the corresponding value of swSysAgentTrapDestinationAddressType, to which the set of traps identified by this entry are to be transmitted.

swSysAgentTrapDestinationTrapMask.name: swSysAgentTrapDestinationTrapMask
swSysAgentTrapDestinationTrapMask.description: This value is a bit string that indicates which traps are enabled for the address identified by this entry. The octet string value is treated as a 64-bit value. The value is a sum. It initially takes on the value 0, then for each trap which is enabled, 2 raised to the value of (swSysAgentTrapDescriptionIndex - 1) for that trap is added to the sum. A new entry in the table is created by setting the value of this object for a new destination address type and destination address. Note that an octet string of all zeros is not a valid value for this object.

swSysAgentTrapDestinationEntryStatus.name: swSysAgentTrapDestinationEntryStatus
swSysAgentTrapDestinationEntryStatus.description: The status of the trap destination table entry. Setting this object to invalid(1) has the effect of removing the corresponding entry from the table.

swSysAgentReadCommunity.name: swSysAgentReadCommunity
swSysAgentReadCommunity.description: This object is the read community string when access is made via SNMP, see RFC1157.

swSysAgentReadWriteCommunity.name: swSysAgentReadWriteCommunity
swSysAgentReadWriteCommunity.description: This object is the read-write community string when access is made via SNMP, see RFC1157. The read-write community string is required to access this object.

swSysInterfaceLocationTable.name: swSysInterfaceLocationTable
swSysInterfaceLocationTable.description: A list of interface location entries. A single entry exists in this list for each interface managed by this agent.

swSysInterfaceLocationEntry.name: swSysInterfaceLocationEntry
swSysInterfaceLocationEntry.description: An interface location entry describes the location of a particular interface managed by this agent.

swSysInterfaceLocationIfIndex.name: swSysInterfaceLocationIfIndex
swSysInterfaceLocationIfIndex.description: The value of the MIB-II ifIndex corresponding to the interface identified by this entry.

swSysInterfaceLocationInterfaceType.name: swSysInterfaceLocationInterfaceType
swSysInterfaceLocationInterfaceType.description: The type of the physical implementation of the interface identified by this entry.

swSysInterfaceLocationType.name: swSysInterfaceLocationType
swSysInterfaceLocationType.description: The type of location where the interface identified by this entry is physically located.

swSysInterfaceLocationTypeIndex.name: swSysInterfaceLocationTypeIndex
swSysInterfaceLocationTypeIndex.description: The index of the location identified by the corresponding instance of swSysInterfaceLocationType where the interface identified by this entry is physically located.

swSysInterfaceLocationLocalIndex.name: swSysInterfaceLocationLocalIndex
swSysInterfaceLocationLocalIndex.description: The local index of the interface identified by this entry relative to its type specified by the corresponding value of swSysInterfaceLocationInterfaceType, and the location specified by the corresponding values of swSysInterfaceLocationType and swSysInterfaceLocationTypeIndex.

swSysInterfaceLocationSystemModuleIndex.name: swSysInterfaceLocationSystemModuleIndex
swSysInterfaceLocationSystemModuleIndex.description: The system module index of the interface idnetified by this entry. Ths index can be used to acquire the module information from the s2SysModuleCardGroup and the swSysDiagnosticsGroup groups.

swSysEthernetPortCount.name: swSysEthernetPortCount
swSysEthernetPortCount.description: The count of ethernet ports managed by this agent.

swSysEthernetPortTable.name: swSysEthernetPortTable
swSysEthernetPortTable.description: A list of ethernet port entries. A single entry exists in this list for each ethernet port managed by this agent.

swSysEthernetPortEntry.name: swSysEthernetPortEntry
swSysEthernetPortEntry.description: An ethernet port entry contains information about a particular ethernet port managed by this agent.

swSysEthernetPortIndex.name: swSysEthernetPortIndex
swSysEthernetPortIndex.description: The index of the ethernet port identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysEthernetPortIfIndex.name: swSysEthernetPortIfIndex
swSysEthernetPortIfIndex.description: The value of the MIB-II ifIndex corresponding to the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysEthernetPortLabel.name: swSysEthernetPortLabel
swSysEthernetPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysEthernetPortLinkStatus.name: swSysEthernetPortLinkStatus
swSysEthernetPortLinkStatus.description: The current value of the link status for the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysEthernetPortType.name: swSysEthernetPortType
swSysEthernetPortType.description: Specific port type description for the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysEthernetPortRateTable.name: swSysEthernetPortRateTable
swSysEthernetPortRateTable.description: A list of ethernet port rate entries. A single entry exists in this list for each ethernet port, managed by this agent, which supports rate information.

swSysEthernetPortRateEntry.name: swSysEthernetPortRateEntry
swSysEthernetPortRateEntry.description: An ethernet port rate entry contains rate statistics for a particular ethernet port managed by this agent. Rate statistics are calculated based on a one second sampling interval.

swSysEthernetPortRateIndex.name: swSysEthernetPortRateIndex
swSysEthernetPortRateIndex.description: The index of the ethernet port identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysEthernetPortRateByteReceiveRate.name: swSysEthernetPortRateByteReceiveRate
swSysEthernetPortRateByteReceiveRate.description: The average number of bytes received per second by the ethernet port identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysEthernetPortRatePeakByteReceiveRate.name: swSysEthernetPortRatePeakByteReceiveRate
swSysEthernetPortRatePeakByteReceiveRate.description: The peak value of swSysEthernetPortRateByteReceiveRate since the system was last initialized for the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysEthernetPortRateFrameReceiveRate.name: swSysEthernetPortRateFrameReceiveRate
swSysEthernetPortRateFrameReceiveRate.description: The average number of frames received per second by the ethernet port identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysEthernetPortRatePeakFrameReceiveRat.name: swSysEthernetPortRatePeakFrameReceiveRate
swSysEthernetPortRatePeakFrameReceiveRat.description: The peak value of swSysEthernetPortRateFrameReceiveRate since the system was last initialized for the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysEthernetPortRateByteTransmitRate.name: swSysEthernetPortRateByteTransmitRate
swSysEthernetPortRateByteTransmitRate.description: The average number of bytes transmitted per second by the ethernet port identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysEthernetPortRatePeakByteTransmitRat.name: swSysEthernetPortRatePeakByteTransmitRate
swSysEthernetPortRatePeakByteTransmitRat.description: The peak value of swSysEthernetPortRateByteTransmitRate since the system was last initialized for the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysEthernetPortRateFrameTransmitRate.name: swSysEthernetPortRateFrameTransmitRate
swSysEthernetPortRateFrameTransmitRate.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second by the ethernet port identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysEthernetPortRatePeakFrameTransmitRa.name: swSysEthernetPortRatePeakFrameTransmitRate
swSysEthernetPortRatePeakFrameTransmitRa.description: The peak value of swSysEthernetPortRateFrameTransmitRate since the system was last initialized for the ethernet port identified by this entry.

swSysSmtCount.name: swSysSmtCount
swSysSmtCount.description: The count of SMTs managed by this agent.

swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconTable.name: swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconTable
swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconTable.description: A list of FDDI MAC beacon entries. A single entry exists in this list for each FDDI MAC, managed by this agent, which supports MAC beacon history.

swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconEntry.name: swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconEntry
swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconEntry.description: An FDDI MAC beacon entry contains information about a particular FDDI MAC's beacon history.

swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconSmtIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconSmtIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconSmtIndex.description: The index of the SMT instance identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconIndex.description: The index of the FDDI MAC identified by this entry, within the SMT identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconHistory.name: swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconHistory
swSysSmtFddiMacBeaconHistory.description: This object gives a history of the most recent beacon information received on the FDDI MAC identified by this entry. It can contain up to a maximum of eight records. Each record is of the form: source MAC: 6 bytes beacon data length: 2 bytes. beacon data: 0-16 bytes.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateTable.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateTable
swSysSmtFddiMacRateTable.description: A list of FDDI MAC rate entries. A single entry exists in this list for each FDDI MAC, managed by this agent, which supports rate statistics.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateEntry.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateEntry
swSysSmtFddiMacRateEntry.description: An FDDI MAC rate entry contains rate statistics for a particular FDDI MAC managed by this agent. Rate statistics are calculated based on a one second sampling interval.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateSmtIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateSmtIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacRateSmtIndex.description: The index of the SMT instance identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacRateIndex.description: The index of the FDDI MAC identified by this entry, within the SMT identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateByteReceiveRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateByteReceiveRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRateByteReceiveRate.description: The average number of bytes received per second by the FDDI MAC identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakByteReceiveRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakByteReceiveRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakByteReceiveRate.description: The peak value of swSysSmtFddiMacByteReceiveRate since the system was last initialized for the FDDI MAC identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateFrameReceiveRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateFrameReceiveRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRateFrameReceiveRate.description: The average number of frames received per second by the FDDI MAC identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakFrameReceiveRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakFrameReceiveRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakFrameReceiveRate.description: The peak value of swSysSmtFddiMacRateFrameReceiveRate since the system was last initialized for the FDDI MAC identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateByteTransmitRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateByteTransmitRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRateByteTransmitRate.description: The average number of bytes transmitted per second by the FDDI MAC identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakByteTransmitRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakByteTransmitRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakByteTransmitRate.description: The peak value of swSysSmtFddiMacByteTransmitRate since the system was last initialized for the FDDI MAC identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacRateFrameTransmitRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRateFrameTransmitRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRateFrameTransmitRate.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second by the FDDI MAC identified by this entry during the most recent sampling period.

swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakFrameTransmitRate.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakFrameTransmitRate
swSysSmtFddiMacRatePeakFrameTransmitRate.description: The peak value of swSysSmtFddiMacFrameTransmitRate since the system was last initialized for the FDDI MAC identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiPortTable.name: swSysSmtFddiPortTable
swSysSmtFddiPortTable.description: A list of FDDI port entries. A single entry exists in this list for each FDDI port managed by this agent.

swSysSmtFddiPortEntry.name: swSysSmtFddiPortEntry
swSysSmtFddiPortEntry.description: An FDDI port entry contains information about a particular FDDI port managed by this agent.

swSysSmtFddiPortSmtIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiPortSmtIndex
swSysSmtFddiPortSmtIndex.description: The index of the SMT instance identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysSmtFddiPortIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiPortIndex
swSysSmtFddiPortIndex.description: The index of the FDDI port identified by this entry, within the SMT identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiPortLocationType.name: swSysSmtFddiPortLocationType
swSysSmtFddiPortLocationType.description: The type of location where the FDDI port identified by this entry is physically located.

swSysSmtFddiPortLocationTypeIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiPortLocationTypeIndex
swSysSmtFddiPortLocationTypeIndex.description: The index of the location identified by the corresponding instance of swSysSmtFddiPortLocationType where the FDDI port identified by this entry is physically located.

swSysSmtFddiPortLocationLocalIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiPortLocationLocalIndex
swSysSmtFddiPortLocationLocalIndex.description: The local index of the FDDI port identified by this entry relative to the location specified by the corresponding values of swSysSmtFddiPortLocationType and swSysSmtFddiPortLocationTypeIndex.

swSysSmtFddiPortLabel.name: swSysSmtFddiPortLabel
swSysSmtFddiPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing the FDDI port identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacLocationTable.name: swSysSmtFddiMacLocationTable
swSysSmtFddiMacLocationTable.description: An FDDI MAC Location table contains information to assign an FDDI MAC to a different Location. The system must be rebooted after all changes to this table are completed in order that the changes take effect.

swSysSmtFddiMacLocationEntry.name: swSysSmtFddiMacLocationEntry
swSysSmtFddiMacLocationEntry.description: An FDDI MAC entry contains information to assign an FDDI MAC to a different Location.

swSysSmtFddiMacLocationSmtIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacLocationSmtIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacLocationSmtIndex.description: The index of the SMT instance identified by this entry, relative to the agent.

swSysSmtFddiMacLocationIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacLocationIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacLocationIndex.description: The index of the FDDI MAC instance identified by this entry, relative to the SMT identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacCurrentLocation.name: swSysSmtFddiMacCurrentLocation
swSysSmtFddiMacCurrentLocation.description: Indicates whether the MAC identified by this entry is assigned to a backplane FDDI station (internal) or an FDDI station configured on a module (external.)

swSysSmtFddiMacRequestedLocation.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRequestedLocation
swSysSmtFddiMacRequestedLocation.description: The Location which the MAC identified by this entry is to be assigned to during the next reboot.

swSysSmtFddiMacAvailableLocation.name: swSysSmtFddiMacAvailableLocation
swSysSmtFddiMacAvailableLocation.description: Indicates the Location(s) available for this MAC. A mac Location which can be modified to either the interanl backplane or an external FDDI port is indicated by internalOrExternal(3).

swSysSmtFddiMacStationTable.name: swSysSmtFddiMacStationTable
swSysSmtFddiMacStationTable.description: An FDDI station MAC table contains information to assign an FDDI MAC to an FDDI Station. The system must be rebooted after all changes to this table are completed in order that the changes take effect.

swSysSmtFddiMacStationEntry.name: swSysSmtFddiMacStationEntry
swSysSmtFddiMacStationEntry.description: An FDDI MAC entry contains information to assign an FDDI MAC to an FDDI Station.

swSysSmtFddiMacStationSmtIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacStationSmtIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacStationSmtIndex.description: The index of the SMT instance identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysSmtFddiMacStationIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiMacStationIndex
swSysSmtFddiMacStationIndex.description: The index of the MAC instance identified by this entry, relative to the SMT identified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiMacCurrentStation.name: swSysSmtFddiMacCurrentStation
swSysSmtFddiMacCurrentStation.description: Indicates which FDDI station that the FDDI MAC identified by this entry is assigned to. A value of 0 indicates that the mac is assigned to an external station. Otherwise the value represents the internal backplane station number.

swSysSmtFddiMacRequestedStation.name: swSysSmtFddiMacRequestedStation
swSysSmtFddiMacRequestedStation.description: Indicates which FDDI station the FDDI MAC identified by this entry will be set to during the next system reboot. A value of 0 indicates an external station. Otherwise the value represents the internal backplane station number.

swSysSmtFddiMacAvailableStations.name: swSysSmtFddiMacAvailableStations
swSysSmtFddiMacAvailableStations.description: This value is a sum. Setting of the first bit (LSB) indicates that the MAC can be assigned to an external station. Available backplane stations are indicated by adding 2^StationNumber to the sum. Where StationNumber represents a backplane station number.

swSysSmtFddiPortStationTable.name: swSysSmtFddiPortStationTable
swSysSmtFddiPortStationTable.description: An FDDI station Port table contains information to assign an FDDI Port to an FDDI Station. The system must be rebooted after all changes to this table are completed in order that the changes take effect.

swSysSmtFddiPortStationEntry.name: swSysSmtFddiPortStationEntry
swSysSmtFddiPortStationEntry.description: An FDDI Port entry contains information to assign an FDDI Port to an FDDI Station.

swSysSmtFddiPortStationSmtIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiPortStationSmtIndex
swSysSmtFddiPortStationSmtIndex.description: The index of the SMT instance identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysSmtFddiPortStationIndex.name: swSysSmtFddiPortStationIndex
swSysSmtFddiPortStationIndex.description: The index of the Port instance identified by this entry, relative to the SMT indentified by this entry.

swSysSmtFddiPortCurrentStation.name: swSysSmtFddiPortCurrentStation
swSysSmtFddiPortCurrentStation.description: Indicates which FDDI station the FDDI Port identified by this entry is assigned to. A value of 0 indicates that the Port is assigned to an external station. Otherwise the value represents the internal backplane station number.

swSysSmtFddiPortRequestedStation.name: swSysSmtFddiPortRequestedStation
swSysSmtFddiPortRequestedStation.description: Indicates which FDDI station the FDDI port identified by this entry will be set to during the next system reboot. A value of 0 indicates an external station. Otherwise the value represents the internal backplane station number.

swSysSmtFddiPortAvailableStations.name: swSysSmtFddiPortAvailableStations
swSysSmtFddiPortAvailableStations.description: This value is a sum. Setting of the first bit indicates that the port can be assigned to an external station. Available backplane stations are indicated by adding 2^StationNumber to the sum. Where StationNumber represents a backplane station number.

swSysBridgeCount.name: swSysBridgeCount
swSysBridgeCount.description: The count of bridges managed by this agent.

swSysBridgeTable.name: swSysBridgeTable
swSysBridgeTable.description: A list of bridge entries. A single entry exists in this list for each bridge managed by this agent.

swSysBridgeEntry.name: swSysBridgeEntry
swSysBridgeEntry.description: A bridge entry contains information about a particular bridge managed by this agent.

swSysBridgeIndex.name: swSysBridgeIndex
swSysBridgeIndex.description: The index of the bridge identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysBridgePortCount.name: swSysBridgePortCount
swSysBridgePortCount.description: The number of bridge ports that the bridge identified by this entry controls.

swSysBridgeAddressTableSize.name: swSysBridgeAddressTableSize
swSysBridgeAddressTableSize.description: The size of the address table for the bridge identified by this entry.

swSysBridgeAddressTableCount.name: swSysBridgeAddressTableCount
swSysBridgeAddressTableCount.description: The current count of addresses in the address table for the bridge identified by this entry.

swSysBridgeAddressTablePeakCount.name: swSysBridgeAddressTablePeakCount
swSysBridgeAddressTablePeakCount.description: The peak count of addresses in the address table for the bridge identified by this entry, since the system was last initialized.

swSysBridgeAddressThreshold.name: swSysBridgeAddressThreshold
swSysBridgeAddressThreshold.description: A reporting threshold for the total number of addresses known for the bridge identified by this entry. When this threshold is reached, the event swSysBridgeAddressThresholdEvent is generated. The range of valid values for setting this object is between 1 and the corresponding value reported by swSysBridgeAddressTableSize + 1 (Note that this range applies to values issued in set requests. The current value may be outside this range, for example if the corresponding value of swSysBridgeMode is changed). Setting this object to one greater than the address table size disables the generation of swSysBridgeAddressThresholdEvents since the limit will never be reached.

swSysBridgeMode.name: swSysBridgeMode
swSysBridgeMode.description: The operational mode of the bridge identified by this entry. Note that bridges which report notSupported(3) will not support sets of this object, and that the value notSupported(3) is not a valid value for a set operation.

swSysBridgeBackbonePort.name: swSysBridgeBackbonePort
swSysBridgeBackbonePort.description: The number of the port selected as the backbone segment port when the corresponding value of swSysBridgeMode is is expressMode(1). The value of this object can range from 1 to the corresponding value of swSysBridgePortCount, however, some bridges may support only a subset of ports as backbone ports. If the corresponding value of swSysBridgeMode is not expressMode(1), the value of this object is ignored.

swSysBridgeIpFragmentationEnabled.name: swSysBridgeIpFragmentationEnabled
swSysBridgeIpFragmentationEnabled.description: A flag indicating whether or not IP fragmentation is enabled on this bridge. Note that bridges which report notSupported(3) will not support sets of this object, and that the value notSupported(3) is not a valid value for a set operation.

swSysBridgeTrFddiTranslationMode.name: swSysBridgeTrFddiTranslationMode
swSysBridgeTrFddiTranslationMode.description: The mode used to describe whether the embedded MAC addresses are byte-conjugated in order to convert them from Token Ring format to native FDDI format (and vice versa), or whether they are left alone (used for traffic flowing across a FDDI backbone to/from Token Ring end stations).

swSysBridgeSTPGroupAddress.name: swSysBridgeSTPGroupAddress
swSysBridgeSTPGroupAddress.description: Spanning tree bridge group address. The address cannot be changed if the spanning tree is enabled (swSysBridgeStpEnabled).

swSysBridgeSTPEnable.name: swSysBridgeSTPEnable
swSysBridgeSTPEnable.description: This object indicates if spanning tree bridge feature is enabled or disabled. If enabled this value will equal true(1).

swSysBridgeIpxSnapTranslationEnable.name: swSysBridgeIpxSnapTranslationEnable
swSysBridgeIpxSnapTranslationEnable.description: This object indicates if the IPX 802.3-FDDI SNAP Translation bridge feature is enabled or disabled. If enabled this value will equal true(1). Note, this object may not be supported on all bridges.

swSysBridgeLowLatencyEnable.name: swSysBridgeLowLatencyEnable
swSysBridgeLowLatencyEnable.description: This object indicates if the bridge low latency feature is enabled or disabled. If enabled this value will equal true(1). Note, this object may not be supported on all bridges.

swSysBridgeVlanMode.name: swSysBridgeVlanMode
swSysBridgeVlanMode.description: This object indicates the VLAN types that this bridge will support. Open mode means that each VLAN within this bridge will be of the Open type; all VLANs within this bridge will share the same address table. Closed mode means that each VLAN within this bridge will be of the Closed type; each VLAN within this bridge will have its own address table. Mixed mode means that each VLAN within this bridge with be of either the Open or Closed type; all Open VLANs will share the same address table and each Closed VLAN will have its own address table.

swSysBridgePortTable.name: swSysBridgePortTable
swSysBridgePortTable.description: A list of bridge port entries. A single entry exists in this list for each bridge port managed by this agent.

swSysBridgePortEntry.name: swSysBridgePortEntry
swSysBridgePortEntry.description: A bridge port entry contains information about a particular bridge port managed by this agent.

swSysBridgePortBridgeIndex.name: swSysBridgePortBridgeIndex
swSysBridgePortBridgeIndex.description: The index of the bridge identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysBridgePortIndex.name: swSysBridgePortIndex
swSysBridgePortIndex.description: The index of the bridge port identified by this entry, within the bridge identified by this entry.

swSysBridgePortIfIndex.name: swSysBridgePortIfIndex
swSysBridgePortIfIndex.description: The value of the MIB-II ifIndex corresponding to the bridge port identified by this entry.

swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit
swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit.description: The maximum number of multicast frames per second that can be received in the sample interval. The sample interval is one second. The default value for this object is zero which implies an infinite rate.

swSysBridgePortAddressAction.name: swSysBridgePortAddressAction
swSysBridgePortAddressAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other(1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: freezeAddress: causes all the learned dynamic addresses to be converted into static addresses. flushAddress: causes all the addresses to be flushed from the address list for the bridge port identified by this entry. flushDynamicAddress: causes all dynamic addresses to be flushed from the address list for the bridge port identified by this entry.

swSysBridgePortSpanningTreeFrameReceived.name: swSysBridgePortSpanningTreeFrameReceivedCounts
swSysBridgePortSpanningTreeFrameReceived.description: The number of spanning tree frames received by the bridge port identified by this entry.

swSysBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards
swSysBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because the receiving bridge port was not in the 'forwarding' state.

swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExce.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceededs
swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExce.description: The number of times the value of swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit was exceeded for the port identified by this entry.

swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExce.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceededDiscards
swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExce.description: The number of multicast/broadcast frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because the corresponding value of swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit was exceeded.

swSysBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards
swSysBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because they contained source addresses which were statically configured on another bridge port. A statically configured address (station), which is not allowed to move, appears to have moved.

swSysBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards
swSysBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because the destination address was unknown. Note that this counter is only valid for backbone ports, and only when the bridge is operating in express mode.

swSysBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards
swSysBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because they contained either invalid (group) source addresses or source addresses belonging to this bridge (indicative of network loops).

swSysBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards
swSysBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because of internal bridge system errors (e.g., hardware and software address table discrepencies).

swSysBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards.name: swSysBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards
swSysBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because the destination address is known on the same network segment as the source address, i.e., the frame does not need to be bridged.

swSysBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards.name: swSysBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards
swSysBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry because the transmitting bridge port was not in the 'forwarding' state.

swSysBridgePortReceiveAllPathFilteredFra.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveAllPathFilteredFrames
swSysBridgePortReceiveAllPathFilteredFra.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry due to user defined receive all path filters.

swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastPathFilte.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastPathFilteredFrames
swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastPathFilte.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry due to user defined receive multicast path filters.

swSysBridgePortTransmitAllPathFilteredFr.name: swSysBridgePortTransmitAllPathFilteredFrames
swSysBridgePortTransmitAllPathFilteredFr.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry due to user defined transmit all path filters.

swSysBridgePortTransmitMulticastPathFilt.name: swSysBridgePortTransmitMulticastPathFilteredFrames
swSysBridgePortTransmitMulticastPathFilt.description: The number of frames discarded by the bridge port identified by this entry due to user defined transmit multicast path filters.

swSysBridgePortForwardedUnicastFrames.name: swSysBridgePortForwardedUnicastFrames
swSysBridgePortForwardedUnicastFrames.description: The number of unicast frames which this port forwarded to a single destination port.

swSysBridgePortForwardedUnicastOctets.name: swSysBridgePortForwardedUnicastOctets
swSysBridgePortForwardedUnicastOctets.description: The number of octets contained in unicast frames which this port forwarded to a single destination port.

swSysBridgePortForwardedMulticastFrames.name: swSysBridgePortForwardedMulticastFrames
swSysBridgePortForwardedMulticastFrames.description: The number of multicast frames which this port forwarded.

swSysBridgePortForwardedMulticastOctets.name: swSysBridgePortForwardedMulticastOctets
swSysBridgePortForwardedMulticastOctets.description: The number of octets contained in multicast frames which this port forwarded.

swSysBridgePortFloodedUnicastFrames.name: swSysBridgePortFloodedUnicastFrames
swSysBridgePortFloodedUnicastFrames.description: The number of unicast frames which this port flooded to all other ports in the bridge.

swSysBridgePortFloodedUnicastOctets.name: swSysBridgePortFloodedUnicastOctets
swSysBridgePortFloodedUnicastOctets.description: The number of octets contained in unicast frames which this port flooded to all other ports in the bridge.

swSysBridgePortStpMode.name: swSysBridgePortStpMode
swSysBridgePortStpMode.reference: IEEE 802.1D-1990: Section 4.5.5.2 for enable and disable modes.
swSysBridgePortStpMode.description: The mode of the bridge port.

swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitFram.name: swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitFrameType
swSysBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitFram.description: This object identifies the frames type(s) that are to be counted when determining if the receive multicast limit has been exceeded for this bridge port. Devices attached to networks with predominantly high multicast traffic (e.g. video) should set this value to broadcastOnly(2) to detect broadcast storms.

swSysBridgePortAddressTable.name: swSysBridgePortAddressTable
swSysBridgePortAddressTable.description: A list of bridge port address information. A single entry exists in this list for each learned address, accross all bridge ports and all bridges managed by this agent.

swSysBridgePortAddressEntry.name: swSysBridgePortAddressEntry
swSysBridgePortAddressEntry.description: An bridge port address entry contains information about a particular bridge port address. To create a new entry, set an instance of swSysBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress with the address index portion of the instance set to 0, to a valid value. To remove an entry, set the instance of the swSysBridgePortAddressType for the entry to invalid(2).

swSysBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex.name: swSysBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex
swSysBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex.description: The index of the bridge identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysBridgePortAddressPortIndex.name: swSysBridgePortAddressPortIndex
swSysBridgePortAddressPortIndex.description: The index of the bridge port identified by this entry, within the bridge identified by this entry.

swSysBridgePortAddressIndex.name: swSysBridgePortAddressIndex
swSysBridgePortAddressIndex.description: The index of this address entry within the bridge address table for the bridge identified by this entry. This index ranges from 1 to the corresponding value of swSysBridgeAddressTableSize.

swSysBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress.name: swSysBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress
swSysBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress.description: The remote MAC address detected on the bridge port identified by to this entry. Setting this object results in an attempt to create a new entry in the table. Since the value of swSysBridgePortAddressIndex is determined automatically internal to the bridge, a set is only successful if the index value specified for swSysBridgePortAddressIndex is zero. A get-next using the values of swSysBridgePortAddressTypeIndex and swSysBridgePortAddressPortIndex can be used to determine the address index assigned to the newly added address entry.

swSysBridgePortAddressType.name: swSysBridgePortAddressType
swSysBridgePortAddressType.description: This object, when read, always returns the value valid(1). Setting this object to invalid(2) will remove the corresponding address entry from the table.

swSysBridgePortAddressIsStatic.name: swSysBridgePortAddressIsStatic
swSysBridgePortAddressIsStatic.description: A value indicating whether this MAC address was statically configured or was dynamically learned. Note that isStatic(1) it the only valid for set operations.

swSysBridgePortAddressStaticPort.name: swSysBridgePortAddressStaticPort
swSysBridgePortAddressStaticPort.description: If the corresponding value of the object swSysBridgePortAddressIsStatic is isStatic(1), this object indicates the local bridge port index (as reported by swSysBridgePortLocalIndex) for which this address MAC was statically configured. If the object swSysBridgePortAddressIsStatic has the value isDynamic(2), the value of this object is 0.

swSysBridgePortAddressAge.name: swSysBridgePortAddressAge
swSysBridgePortAddressAge.description: This object indicates the time, in seconds, elapsed since a packet containing this address as a source was last seen on the bridge port identified by this entry.

swSysBridgeStpGroupAddress.name: swSysBridgeStpGroupAddress
swSysBridgeStpGroupAddress.description: Spanning tree bridge group address. The address cannot be changed if the spanning tree is enabled (swSysBridgeStpEnabled). This object can now be found under the swSysBridgeTable as swSysBridgeSTPGroupAddress.

swSysBridgeStpEnable.name: swSysBridgeStpEnable
swSysBridgeStpEnable.description: This object indicates if spanning tree bridge feature is enabled or disabled. If enabled this value will equal true(1). This object can now be found under the swSysBridgeTable as swSysBridgeSTPEnable.

swSysNetworkAnalyzerTable.name: swSysNetworkAnalyzerTable
swSysNetworkAnalyzerTable.description: A list of analyzer entries. A single entry exists in this list for each bridge port configured for an analyzer.

swSysNetworkAnalyzerTableEntry.name: swSysNetworkAnalyzerTableEntry
swSysNetworkAnalyzerTableEntry.description: An analyzer table entry contains information relating an analyzer port address to the bridge and port index for that analyzer. The effect of creating an entry for a particular port is to configure that port for monitoring. A port which is configured for monitoring is no longer available for switching. To create an entry, set the value of the swSysNetworkAnalyzerStatus object for a non-existent instance to valid(1). The value of the swSysNetworkAnalyzerPhysicalAddress object for the new entry is filled in as a result of the creation. The effect of removing an entry for a particular port is to disable the port for monitoring. The port is then available for switching. To remove an entry, set the value of the corresponding instance of the swSysNetworkAnalyzerStatus object to invalid(2).

swSysNetworkAnalyzerBridgeIndex.name: swSysNetworkAnalyzerBridgeIndex
swSysNetworkAnalyzerBridgeIndex.description: The index of the bridge relative to this agent where the analyzer identified by this entry is configured.

swSysNetworkAnalyzerBridgePortIndex.name: swSysNetworkAnalyzerBridgePortIndex
swSysNetworkAnalyzerBridgePortIndex.description: The index of the port relative to the bridge identified by this entry where the analyzer identified by this entry is configured.

swSysNetworkAnalyzerPhysicalAddress.name: swSysNetworkAnalyzerPhysicalAddress
swSysNetworkAnalyzerPhysicalAddress.description: The physical address of the bridge port identified by the corresponding values of swSysNetworkAnalyzerBridgeIndex and swSysNetworkAnayzerBridgePortIndex.

swSysNetworkAnalyzerStatus.name: swSysNetworkAnalyzerStatus
swSysNetworkAnalyzerStatus.description: The status of the entry. Setting the value of a non-existent instance of this object to valid(1) attempts to add the corresponding entry to the table. The effect of adding an entry to the table is to configure the port for monitoring and to disable it for switching. Setting an existing instance of this object to invalid(2) attempts to remove the corresponding entry from the table. The effect of removing an entry from the table is to disable the port for monitoring and to make available for switching.

swSysNetworkPortMonitorTable.name: swSysNetworkPortMonitorTable
swSysNetworkPortMonitorTable.description: A list of monitor port entries. A single entry exists in this for each bridge port being monitored.

swSysNetworkPortMonitorTableEntry.name: swSysNetworkPortMonitorTableEntry
swSysNetworkPortMonitorTableEntry.description: A port monitor table entry contains information relating a bridge port being monitored with the address of the analyzer which is being used to monitor the port. The effect of creating an entry for a particular port is to enable monitoring of that port by the analyzer specified. To create an entry, set the value of the swSysNetworkPortMonitorAnalyzerAddress object to the address of the network analyzer port. This value should be the same as the value of the swSysNetworkAnalyzerPhysicalAddress object for the analyzer. The effect of removing an entry for a particular port is to disable monitoring of that port. To remove an entry, set the value of the corresponding instance of the swSysNetworkPortMonitorStatus object to invalid(2).

swSysNetworkPortMonitorBridgeIndex.name: swSysNetworkPortMonitorBridgeIndex
swSysNetworkPortMonitorBridgeIndex.description: The index of the bridge relative to this agent where the monitored port identified by this entry is located.

swSysNetworkPortMonitorBridgePortIndex.name: swSysNetworkPortMonitorBridgePortIndex
swSysNetworkPortMonitorBridgePortIndex.description: The index of the port which is being monitored relative to the bridge identified by this entry.

swSysNetworkPortMonitorAnalyzerAddress.name: swSysNetworkPortMonitorAnalyzerAddress
swSysNetworkPortMonitorAnalyzerAddress.description: The physical address of the port where the analyzer, which is monitoring the port identified by this entry, is located. Setting the value of a non-existent instance of this object attempts to add an entry to the table. The effect of adding an entry to the table is to enable monitoring of the port by the analyzer specified. Setting the value of an existing instance of this object will switch the monitored port to the new analyzer address.

swSysNetworkPortMonitorStatus.name: swSysNetworkPortMonitorStatus
swSysNetworkPortMonitorStatus.description: The status of the entry. Setting an existing instance of this object to invalid(2) attempts to remove the corresponding entry from the table. The effect of removing an entry from the table is to disable monitoring of the port.

swSysTokenRingPortCount.name: swSysTokenRingPortCount
swSysTokenRingPortCount.description: The count of token ring ports managed by this agent.

swSysTokenRingPortTable.name: swSysTokenRingPortTable
swSysTokenRingPortTable.description: A list of token ring port entries. A single entry exists in this list for each token ring port managed by this agent.

swSysTokenRingPortEntry.name: swSysTokenRingPortEntry
swSysTokenRingPortEntry.description: A token ring port entry contains information about a particular token ring port managed by this agent.

swSysTokenRingPortIndex.name: swSysTokenRingPortIndex
swSysTokenRingPortIndex.description: The index of the token ring port identified by this entry, relative to this agent.

swSysTokenRingPortIfIndex.name: swSysTokenRingPortIfIndex
swSysTokenRingPortIfIndex.description: The value of the MIB-II ifIndex corresponding to the token ring port identified by this entry.

swSysTokenRingPortLabel.name: swSysTokenRingPortLabel
swSysTokenRingPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing the token ring port identified by this entry.

swSysTokenRingPortInsertStatus.name: swSysTokenRingPortInsertStatus
swSysTokenRingPortInsertStatus.description: The current value of the link status for the token ring port identified by this entry.

swSysTokenRingPortACErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station receives an AMP or SMP frame in which A is equal to C is equal to 0, and then receives another SMP frame with A is equal to C is equal to 0 without first receiving an AMP frame. swSysTokenRingPortAbortTransErrors.name: swSysTokenRingPortAbortTransErrors

swSysTokenRingPortInternalErrors.name: swSysTokenRingPortInternalErrors

swSysTokenRingPortReceiveCongestionError.name: swSysTokenRingPortReceiveCongestionErrors

swSysTokenRingPortFrameCopiedErrors.name: swSysTokenRingPortFrameCopiedErrors
swSysTokenRingPortFrameCopiedErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station recognizes a frame addressed to its specific address and detects that the FS field A bits are set to 1 indicating a possible line hit or duplicate address.

swSysTokenRingPortTokenErrors.name: swSysTokenRingPortTokenErrors
swSysTokenRingPortTokenErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station acting as the active monitor recognizes an error condition that needs a token transmitted.

swSysTokenRingPortRemoves.name: swSysTokenRingPortRemoves

swSysTokenRingPortSingles.name: swSysTokenRingPortSingles
swSysTokenRingPortSingles.description: The number of times the interface has sensed that it is the only station on the ring. This will happen if the interface is the first one up on a ring, or if there is a hardware problem.

swSysTokenRingPortFreqErrors.name: swSysTokenRingPortFreqErrors
swSysTokenRingPortFreqErrors.description: The number of times the interface has detected that the frequency of the incoming signal differs from the expected frequency.

swSysTokenRingPortRingStatus.name: swSysTokenRingPortRingStatus
swSysTokenRingPortRingStatus.description: The current interface status which can be used to diagnose fluctuating problems that can occur on token rings, after a station has successfully been added to the ring. Before an open is completed, this object has the value for the 'no status' condition. This object is useful for debugging problems when the station can not even enter the ring. The object's value is a sum of values, one for each currently applicable condition. Setting this object to createAndWait(5) causes an entry to be created with swSysFtRowStatus value of notReady(3). Setting this object to active(1) causes the transfer to start for the given row.
